This paper focuses on improving the accuracy of a system that captures and analyzes motion data during a cognitive assessment game for children. The paper is likely to fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category, as it involves designing a game-like assessment method for children. The paper also involves machine learning techniques to analyze motion data, which could fall under the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
